# bad_cancel_paths
# ================
# One regex per line, matched against Path information only for cancel control
# messages. This is local policy; Cancel-Lock and Cancel-Key verification stays
# in INN and is intentionally not duplicated here.
#
# Exact untrusted injection token:
# (?:^|!)reader\.untrusted-peer\.example(?:!|$)
#
# Exact host with optional literal .POSTED suffix:
# (?:^|!)reader\.untrusted-peer\.example(?:\.POSTED)?(?:!|$)
#
# Numbered abusive cancel source:
# (?:^|!)cancel-source[0-9]{1,3}\.example(?:!|$)
#
# Two exact sources:
# (?:^|!)(?:cancel-a|cancel-b)\.example\.net(?:!|$)
#
# Do not block a complete provider until you understand its cancel policy and
# have checked INN's native authenticated-cancel handling.
